values:
The Leipzig photograph reminded me of Irina Mariescu. She was a prostitute in Kishinev who I dated for three months when I was just 18. She was 42 and very experienced. I learned a lot from her. Sex, card games, tin whistle, hula hooping and more else. Alas she died when she was 51 years old. They said she had a bad chest, but I thought her chest was quite good for her age.

I am sorry. It is bad joke and in poor spirit. I raise my class of cider to her memory. Szulte Irina. What is cider? It tastes like apples which have been kept in a bag behind the oil radiator of an old womans&nbsp;tenement building apartment. If that is hopw it is made then I shall not&nbsp;drink it any more.&nbsp;

Friend Michael says this is how it is made in a place called Falmouth.
